<p>If I do the following, do we really need comments and documentation? Won't the code be a good documentation?</p>  <p>1) the method names and variable names are defined correctly according to the context 2) the size of the method and class is small and meaningful</p>  <p>The following are the issues of the documentation. 1) The documentation need to be updated as we update the code.  2) If the code itself is good documentation, it is waste of productivity.</p>